.TH RCAT 1 "May 2026" "rcat" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rcat \- render Markdown (and many other source/config files) in the terminal
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rcat
.RI [ OPTIONS "] [" FILE "...]"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rcat
reads each
.I FILE
and writes a styled, terminal-friendly rendering to standard output. With no
.I FILE,
or when
.I FILE
is
.RB ` - ',
the standard input is used.
.PP
By default,
.B rcat
treats input as
.B CommonMark
Markdown (with GFM extensions: tables, task lists, autolinks, strikethrough).
When the input filename does not look like Markdown \(em or when
.B \-\-lang
forces a different language \(em
.B rcat
falls back to its built-in syntax highlighter, which knows ~60 languages and
configuration formats. Run
.B rcat \-\-lang list
to print every recognised alias.
.PP
Code fences inside Markdown are syntax-highlighted with the same engine.
Images referenced from Markdown are decoded and rendered as Unicode
half-block art via
.BR chafa .
Image paths are resolved relative to each
.IR FILE 's
directory; remote
.B http(s)
URLs are only fetched when
.B \-\-allow\-web
is given.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a short help message (translated when a matching locale catalog is
installed) and exit.
.TP
.BR \-c " " \fIN\fR ", " \-\-columns " " \fIN\fR
Wrap output to
.I N
columns. Defaults to the terminal width as reported by
.BR TIOCGWINSZ ,
or to 80 if stdout is not a TTY. The
.B COLUMNS
environment variable overrides autodetection.
Values below 10 are rejected.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-plain
Strip all styling: no SGR escapes, no Unicode box-drawing, no hyperlinks.
Output is just word-wrapped text.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-color
Disable colour but keep other styling (Unicode bullets, headings, etc.).
Equivalent to setting
.BR NO_COLOR =1.
.TP
.B \-\-force\-color
Emit colour even when stdout is not a TTY. Useful when piping into
.B less \-R.
.TP
.B \-\-color " " \fIMODE\fR
Force the colour mode. One of
.BR auto ,
.BR none ,
.BR 16 ,
.B 256
or
.BR truecolor .
.B auto
defers to terminal autodetection (the default).
.TP
.B \-\-no\-hyperlinks
Never emit OSC 8 hyperlinks, even when the terminal advertises support.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-images
Skip inline images even when image rendering was compiled in.
.TP
.B \-\-allow\-web
Download and render
.B http(s)
image URLs. Off by default. Each fetch is capped at the
.B \-\-web\-timeout
seconds and 16 MiB.
.TP
.B \-\-web\-timeout " " \fISEC\fR
Per-image fetch timeout for
.B \-\-allow\-web,
in seconds. Default 10. Values below 1 are rejected.
.TP
.B \-\-image\-height " " \fIN\fR
Cap rendered image height to
.I N
terminal rows. Default 20. Width scales to preserve aspect ratio.
.TP
.B \-\-ascii
Force ASCII-only output. No box-drawing characters, no bullet glyphs;
useful for legacy terminals or pipelines into ASCII-only tools.
.TP
.B \-\-lang " " \fILANG\fR
Force the input language regardless of filename or extension. Use
.B md
or
.B markdown
to run the Markdown renderer explicitly. Use
.B list
to print every alias the highlighter recognises and exit.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B NO_COLOR
If set to any value, disables colour. Honoured even when stdout is a TTY.
.TP
.B COLUMNS
Overrides the autodetected terminal width.
.TP
.BR LANG ", " LC_ALL ", " LC_CTYPE ", " LC_MESSAGES
Drive locale selection for translated messages and Unicode detection. A
locale whose codeset contains
.B UTF-8
or
.B utf8
enables Unicode box-drawing and bullets.
.TP
.B RCAT_LOCALEDIR
Override the directory
.B gettext
searches for compiled message catalogs
.RB ( rcat.mo ).
Defaults to the install prefix's
.B share/locale
directory. Useful when running the binary out of a build tree.
.TP
.BR TERM ", " COLORTERM ", " TERM_PROGRAM ", " SSH_TTY ", " SSH_CONNECTION
Used to detect colour depth, OSC 8 hyperlink support, and whether the
session is over SSH.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
One or more input files could not be read or could not be parsed.
.TP
.B 2
Invalid command-line usage (unknown option, malformed value).
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Render this manual's source:
.PP
.RS
.nf
rcat README.md
.fi
.RE
.PP
Pretty-print any source file, like
.B cat:
.PP
.RS
.nf
rcat src/rcat.cpp
rcat Dockerfile
rcat /etc/hosts
.fi
.RE
.PP
Pipe a remote document with colour preserved:
.PP
.RS
.nf
curl -fsSL https://example.com/post.md | rcat --force-color - | less -R
.fi
.RE
.PP
Force a specific language:
.PP
.RS
.nf
rcat --lang yaml config.txt
.fi
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I @CMAKE_INSTALL_FULL_LOCALEDIR@/<lang>/LC_MESSAGES/rcat.mo
Compiled message catalogs for translated UI strings.
.SH BUGS
Report issues at the project's tracker. See
.B SECURITY.md
in the source tree for the responsible-disclosure process for security
issues.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR cat (1),
.BR less (1),
.BR md4c (3),
.BR chafa (1),
.BR locale (1).
